00:52:42.710 --> 00:52:44.159
So we're going to have one more
step of this,

00:52:44.159 --> 00:52:47.289
but this is the high watermark
of the standard,

00:52:47.289 --> 00:52:51.380
you know, the finance guys who
made finance such an important

00:52:51.380 --> 00:52:54.594
subject,
and the rational expectations

00:52:54.594 --> 00:52:56.210
school of finance.
 

00:52:56.210 --> 00:52:58.460
This is kind of the most clever
thing that they did.

00:52:58.460 --> 00:53:02.876
So this kind of reasoning,
bookies maybe knew it for a

00:53:02.876 --> 00:53:05.652
long time,
but Black-Scholes in 1973

00:53:05.652 --> 00:53:09.512
started this kind of thinking
and then lots of hedge funds

00:53:09.512 --> 00:53:12.289
started imitating it including
my own.

00:53:12.289 --> 00:53:16.239
So I certainly didn't invent
this idea of dynamic hedging.

00:53:16.239 --> 00:53:20.469
Now, let's take a step back.
 

00:53:20.469 --> 00:53:23.510
The crucial idea is marking to
market.

00:53:23.510 --> 00:53:26.407
The crucial idea is that you
want to hedge something through

00:53:26.407 --> 00:53:29.550
millions of scenarios and really
the outcome you won't know until

00:53:29.550 --> 00:53:30.139
the end.
 

00:53:30.139 --> 00:53:35.393
What you should do is hedge at
each step of the way your mark

00:53:35.393 --> 00:53:36.969
to market value.
 

00:53:36.969 --> 00:53:39.489
So you only have to do things a
step at a time.

00:53:39.489 --> 00:53:42.318
There's an exponentially
growing number of paths,

00:53:42.318 --> 00:53:45.382
but there are only two
possibilities from today until

00:53:45.382 --> 00:53:46.150
tomorrow.
 

00:53:46.150 --> 00:53:48.268
So it's very simple to hedge
two things.

00:53:48.268 --> 00:53:52.195
It seems incredibly complicated
to hedge 2 to the 100 things,

00:53:52.195 --> 00:53:55.599
2 to the 10th is a very big
number, 2 is a very small

00:53:55.599 --> 00:53:56.320
number.
 

00:53:56.320 --> 00:53:57.518
You can hedge two things.
 

00:53:57.518 --> 00:54:00.657
It may be very complicated to
hedge 2 to the 10 things,

00:54:00.657 --> 00:54:03.619
but you only have to hedge 2
things on every day.

00:54:03.619 --> 00:54:05.963
So once you've realized that,
hedging is actually quite a

00:54:05.963 --> 00:54:06.760
simple operation.
 

00:54:06.760 --> 00:54:10.201
You don't have to do it by
trading in the interest rate

00:54:10.201 --> 00:54:11.539
