00:56:42.782 --> 00:56:48.219
22,24, 23, about 23 dollars,
1 sixth of the bond.

00:56:48.219 --> 00:56:51.519
So if you took the other 98.8
dollars and put it to the 1 year

00:56:51.519 --> 00:56:54.197
Treasury,
I claim it's obvious--so take 1

00:56:54.197 --> 00:57:00.994
sixth of the--
so 1 sixth of 30 year 9 percent

00:57:00.994 --> 00:57:02.119
bond.
 

00:57:02.119 --> 00:57:08.929
That's 1 sixth of this thing,
which costs you what?

00:57:08.929 --> 00:57:12.139
It cost 23 dollars.
 

00:57:12.139 --> 00:57:13.610
The price of that is 23 dollars.
 

00:57:13.610 --> 00:57:24.922
Now, combine that with 75.8
dollars of 1 year Treasury,

00:57:24.922 --> 00:57:30.789
