00:58:59.710 --> 00:59:01.965
9 percent bond,
but I could always reproduce

00:59:01.965 --> 00:59:03.329
these same two payments.
 

00:59:03.329 --> 00:59:06.664
So I don't have to hedge by
holding derivatives,

00:59:06.664 --> 00:59:10.710
interest rate derivatives,
I can hedge by holding standard

00:59:10.710 --> 00:59:11.420
bonds.
 

00:59:11.420 --> 00:59:15.940
And I can tell at a glance how
much of the longer term bond to

00:59:15.940 --> 00:59:20.016
hold because I just have to
match this gap in the prices

00:59:20.016 --> 00:59:24.538
since the 1 year bond is always
going to pay the same thing up

00:59:24.538 --> 00:59:25.650
and down.
 

00:59:25.650 --> 00:59:32.579
Did that go too fast?
 

00:59:32.579 --> 00:59:33.559
Yeah?
 

00:59:33.559 --> 00:59:34.844
Student: I know it's
just

00:59:34.844 --> 00:59:36.045
like&gt;
 

00:59:36.045 --> 00:59:38.739
but how did you figure out how
