00:59:38.739 --> 00:59:44.360
Prof: So I want to hold
1 sixth of the 30 year bond,

00:59:44.360 --> 00:59:49.306
which cost me 140,
so 1 sixth of that is going to

00:59:49.306 --> 00:59:51.469
cost me 23 dollars.
 

00:59:51.469 --> 00:59:57.036
All right, now I want to also
hold a 1 year Treasury so that

00:59:57.036 --> 01:00:02.793
the payment 1 sixth of 121 at
the top plus whatever the 1 year

01:00:02.793 --> 01:00:07.983
Treasury pays me is equal to
100.6 and such that 1 sixth

01:00:07.983 --> 01:00:12.639
times this value at the bottom,
oh, sorry.

01:00:12.639 --> 01:00:15.250
It's 1 sixth this coupon is
paying.

01:00:15.250 --> 01:00:17.269
Actually it wasn't 121.6.
 

01:00:17.269 --> 01:00:19.219
It's a 9 percent bond.
 

01:00:19.219 --> 01:00:21.590
I forgot its coupon,
